cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition using an attention-based encoder-decoder model. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speaker adaptation for speech recognition. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes regularization-based approaches for speaker adaptation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with end-to-end speech recognition using deep learning techniques. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with social or network-related aspects, but it is still a possible category as the paper deals with information processing in the form of speech recognition.
